new file mode 100644
index 0000000..ed7c481
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/runbooks/webhook-replays.md
@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@
+# Webhook replay recovery
+
+Replay workers acquire a two-minute database lease before sending a failed delivery.
+Only the worker returned by the claim statement may continue with delivery.
+Postgres supplies both claim and expiry time so regional process clocks cannot change the lease.
+
+## Rollout checks
+
+1. Enable `atomic_replay_claims` in one region.
+2. Watch `webhook_duplicate_delivery_total` for 24 hours.
+3. Confirm expired claims return to the pending replay queue.
+4. Compare claim duration across at least two worker regions.
+5. Expand the flag to the remaining regions.
+
+Do not delete an active claim manually. Stop the owning worker and allow the lease to expire so
+the next worker acquires ownership through the same atomic path.
